         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">31/8/82. ¶  ¶ This day, dear Prof Liversidge, I receive the two copies of your new volume of the R.S. of N S Wales ¶  from the Melbourne public Library, when my Assistant happened to call there. Possi...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.08.31</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Archibald Liversidge</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS 9077, Box 65, Royal Society of NSW papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of NSW, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">31/8/82.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day, dear Prof Liversidge, I receive the two copies of your new volume of the R.S. of N S Wales<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Journal and Proceedings of the Royal Society of NSW</seg>, vol. 15.</p>
               </note> from the Melbourne public Library, when my Assistant happened to call there. Possibly these books were there for some time; if so — then pardon, that I not earlier acknowledged this kind sending. When such a number of valuable papers were presented to the Society, I must feel especially grateful for having so much space accorded to my contribution.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B82.07.05; <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M’s paper occupied pp. 185-300.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Let me also express my best thanks for the copy of Major Richard’s excellent book “NSW in 1881”<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Richards (1882).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
